cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

The paper deals with fine-grained categorisation, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a learning system that involves deep convolutional neural networks, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses clustering and transfer learning, which are topics covered in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The experiments involve image classification, which is a topic in cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper also discusses the use of features for classification, which is a topic in cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
